Information for Beneficiaries

   Welcome to the Health Care Financing Administration's Beneficiary
   information page. This page is the first stop for Medicare, Medicaid,
   and SCHIP (State Children's Health Insurance Program) beneficiaries,
   family members, and caregivers.

   Below are some links to important beneficiary information HCFA provides
   online. Remember, though, that the list only includes our suggestions.
   If you can't find what you're looking for below, try out our search
   tool.

   HCFA's consumer information for the Medicare program can be found on
   our Beneficiary website at www.medicare.gov. The Medicare-related links
   below will take you to this site.

   I am looking for information on:
     * Medicare
     * Medicaid
     * State Children's Health Insurance
     * HCFA's Maternal AIDS Consumer Information

   I would like to:
     * find local contacts
     * report suspected Medicare fraud or Medicaid fraud
     * get a Medicare Handbook (PDF format) or other beneficiary
       publication
     * find out more about managed care plans in my area
     * find out more about nursing homes in my area
     * find answers to my questions
     * get information about protecting my health insurance
     * find more health information from the Federal Government

